name: La Bastide
description:
Le secret du restaurant Edouard Loubet n'est pas que dans une cuisine gastronomique fruit de la créativité d'un jeune chef. Il réside aussi dans un cadre exceptionnel : une bastide provençale plantée au milieu des champs de lavande qui appelle au calme et à l'élégance.

Dans les cuisines, Edouard Loubet compose des plats au rythme des saisons. Ce chef d'orchestre crée des mélodies provençales avec des accords de saveurs et de couleurs. Sarriette, arquebuse, lavande et sauge chantent à l'unisson dans les assiettes.

Découvrez ces chefs d'œuvre de la gastronomie française.

name: Agapé
description:
"PLAIN-MONCEAU - in the triangle Malesherbes, Wagram, Villiers, Agapé offers the welcome of a reference restaurant in a dining room full of nuance and elegance.

SUBTLE ALCHEMY - At L'Agapé, the gourmet cuisine respects the product and flavors. The dishes are tasty, classic and refined. The restaurant offers gourmets exceptional seasonal products. Chef Toshitaka Omiya, faithful to the spirit of the place, works the textures, tastes, temperatures, spices he combines subtly.

SAFE VALUE - Desserts also compose a beautiful partition of Agapé's menu. The entire talent of pastry chef Rikako Kobayashi is expressed in the smooth and surprising preparations."

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

name: Ria Formosa Restaurante
description:
The Ria Formosa Lounge Bar and Restaurant, on the Hotel Faro's rooftop terrace, afford a breathtaking panoramic view over the city and the Ria Formosa. Regardless of the time of day or the season, this is always a sophisticated and inviting place in which to relax by yourself or socialise with others.

An extensive selection of high-quality breakfast items are served here from 7.30 am to 10.30 am. Lunch at the Ria Formosa Restaurant is served from 12.30 pm to 3 pm. This is the perfect place for both businesspeople and groups of friends to have lunch or to relax after a visit to the city's historical sites. Dinner is served from 7.30 pm to 10.30 pm, but we suggest you arrive in plenty of time to enjoy a pre-dinner drink or cocktail while you marvel at the magnificent sunset.

name: La Bastide
description:
Le secret du restaurant Edouard Loubet n'est pas que dans une cuisine gastronomique fruit de la créativité d'un jeune chef. Il réside aussi dans un cadre exceptionnel : une bastide provençale plantée au milieu des champs de lavande qui appelle au calme et à l'élégance.

Dans les cuisines, Edouard Loubet compose des plats au rythme des saisons. Ce chef d'orchestre crée des mélodies provençales avec des accords de saveurs et de couleurs. Sarriette, arquebuse, lavande et sauge chantent à l'unisson dans les assiettes.

Découvrez ces chefs d'œuvre de la gastronomie française.

name: Magenta
description: This restaurant is located within a former bank and its faux-industrial interior celebrates the history of the area, with an evocative design featuring hundreds of brightly coloured butterflies. The understated, modern Italian dishes take their influences from Northern Italy.

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

name: Agapé
description:
"PLAIN-MONCEAU - in the triangle Malesherbes, Wagram, Villiers, Agapé offers the welcome of a reference restaurant in a dining room full of nuance and elegance.

SUBTLE ALCHEMY - At L'Agapé, the gourmet cuisine respects the product and flavors. The dishes are tasty, classic and refined. The restaurant offers gourmets exceptional seasonal products. Chef Toshitaka Omiya, faithful to the spirit of the place, works the textures, tastes, temperatures, spices he combines subtly.

SAFE VALUE - Desserts also compose a beautiful partition of Agapé's menu. The entire talent of pastry chef Rikako Kobayashi is expressed in the smooth and surprising preparations."

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

name: La Bastide
description:
Le secret du restaurant Edouard Loubet n'est pas que dans une cuisine gastronomique fruit de la créativité d'un jeune chef. Il réside aussi dans un cadre exceptionnel : une bastide provençale plantée au milieu des champs de lavande qui appelle au calme et à l'élégance.

Dans les cuisines, Edouard Loubet compose des plats au rythme des saisons. Ce chef d'orchestre crée des mélodies provençales avec des accords de saveurs et de couleurs. Sarriette, arquebuse, lavande et sauge chantent à l'unisson dans les assiettes.

Découvrez ces chefs d'œuvre de la gastronomie française.

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

description:

SUBTLE ALCHEMY - At L'Agapé, the gourmet cuisine respects the product and flavors. The dishes are tasty, classic and refined. The restaurant offers gourmets exceptional seasonal products. Chef Toshitaka Omiya, faithful to the spirit of the place, works the textures, tastes, temperatures, spices he combines subtly.

SAFE VALUE - Desserts also compose a beautiful partition of Agapé's menu. The entire talent of pastry chef Rikako Kobayashi is expressed in the smooth and surprising preparations."

name: Le Bouzou
description:
Voici l'adresse pour vivre un véritable repas festif. Côté cuisine, c'est un festival de spécialités de régions lointaines  (africaine, indienne, malgache, réunionnaise et asiatique). Côté salle, l'ambiance est toujours au rendez-vous pour tout type d'événements (anniversaire, enterrement de vie de jeune fille ou de garçon).

Pour une ambiance conviviale, profitez du buffet à volonté qui déploiera tout un panel de spécialités exotiques. En tout, 40 entrées et 40 plats de poissons, viandes et végétariens comme la salade de quinoa et poivrons doux piquillos ou encore l'antilope au tamarin.

Et pour continuer jusqu'au bout de la nuit, tous les samedis, des soirées dansantes sont organisées.

name: La Bastide
description:
Le secret du restaurant Edouard Loubet n'est pas que dans une cuisine gastronomique fruit de la créativité d'un jeune chef. Il réside aussi dans un cadre exceptionnel : une bastide provençale plantée au milieu des champs de lavande qui appelle au calme et à l'élégance.

Dans les cuisines, Edouard Loubet compose des plats au rythme des saisons. Ce chef d'orchestre crée des mélodies provençales avec des accords de saveurs et de couleurs. Sarriette, arquebuse, lavande et sauge chantent à l'unisson dans les assiettes.

Découvrez ces chefs d'œuvre de la gastronomie française.

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

description:
La Truffe dans tous ses Etats est situé entre Aix en Provence et Marseille, l'unique établissement de la région spécialisé dans la cuisine de la truffe.

Avis aux épicuriens, la gastronomie s'invite à votre table à moindre coût, les meilleurs opportunités du marché suggérées selon l'inspiration du moment. La truffe se décline toute l'année; vous profiterez d'un travail artisanal de la confection du pain à la réalisation de vos sorbets. Le diamant noir vous sera suggéré sous toutes ses formes, vous apprécierez  la Truffe dans tous ses états…

Côté restaurant, vous découvrirez un jardin verdoyant, un lieu exceptionnel et intimiste dédié à la sérénité,  une décoration intérieure réalisée avec goût et finesse. La cuisine ouverte permet de profiter des effluves gourmandes. Les maîtres mots « Partage & Convivialité ».

name: Zambeze
address: Calçada do Marquês de Tancos, Ed EMEL,1100-340,Lisboa
description:
Zambeze, a river of African inspiration. Located in the historical centre of Lisbon, between ‘Largo do Caldas' and ‘S. Jorge' castle, Zambeze Restaurant offers an exquisite view between downtown Lisbon and the Tagus river. The restaurant is set on the top floor of the restored former market ‘Chão do Loureiro'. Zambeze Restaurant combines the best regional cuisine of Central Portugal, with the unique and intense African flavours.
The decoration enhances traditional elements of the Portuguese culture, including Bordallo Pinheiro porcelain pieces inside and two “azulejos“ (glazed tiles) panels outside, created by the artist Paulo Ossião.
Outside, settled within a magnificent surrounding, the terrace is the perfect place to enjoy a modern and relaxed evening.

name: Chapitô à Mesa - Restaurante
description:
Located right bellow the walls of São Jorge Castle, Chapitô offers the visitor a dazzling sight over the city and the river.
Chapitô is non-profit and non-governmental organization for development, promoting social inclusion and professional training of youngsters, through the performing arts.  
Chapitô practices a social economy financially supported by the production, creation and direction of shows/events, along with the income of public places such as our restaurant Chapitô à Mesa.
There, you will enjoy the specialties of Chef Bertílio, a reference of the contemporary Portuguese cuisine. The environment is unique, combining three different Portuguese concepts in a single space.
You may then choose to eat indoors or outdoors, on the belvedere area or the terrace, considered the 7th best in the world, and referenced by different international tourist agencies.

name: La Bastide
description:
Le secret du restaurant Edouard Loubet n'est pas que dans une cuisine gastronomique fruit de la créativité d'un jeune chef. Il réside aussi dans un cadre exceptionnel : une bastide provençale plantée au milieu des champs de lavande qui appelle au calme et à l'élégance.

Dans les cuisines, Edouard Loubet compose des plats au rythme des saisons. Ce chef d'orchestre crée des mélodies provençales avec des accords de saveurs et de couleurs. Sarriette, arquebuse, lavande et sauge chantent à l'unisson dans les assiettes.

Découvrez ces chefs d'œuvre de la gastronomie française.

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

description:

SUBTLE ALCHEMY - At L'Agapé, the gourmet cuisine respects the product and flavors. The dishes are tasty, classic and refined. The restaurant offers gourmets exceptional seasonal products. Chef Toshitaka Omiya, faithful to the spirit of the place, works the textures, tastes, temperatures, spices he combines subtly.

SAFE VALUE - Desserts also compose a beautiful partition of Agapé's menu. The entire talent of pastry chef Rikako Kobayashi is expressed in the smooth and surprising preparations."

description:
Voici l'adresse pour vivre un véritable repas festif. Côté cuisine, c'est un festival de spécialités de régions lointaines  (africaine, indienne, malgache, réunionnaise et asiatique). Côté salle, l'ambiance est toujours au rendez-vous pour tout type d'événements (anniversaire, enterrement de vie de jeune fille ou de garçon).

Pour une ambiance conviviale, profitez du buffet à volonté qui déploiera tout un panel de spécialités exotiques. En tout, 40 entrées et 40 plats de poissons, viandes et végétariens comme la salade de quinoa et poivrons doux piquillos ou encore l'antilope au tamarin.

Et pour continuer jusqu'au bout de la nuit, tous les samedis, des soirées dansantes sont organisées.

name: La Truffe dans Tous ses États
description:
La Truffe dans tous ses Etats est situé entre Aix en Provence et Marseille, l'unique établissement de la région spécialisé dans la cuisine de la truffe.

Avis aux épicuriens, la gastronomie s'invite à votre table à moindre coût, les meilleurs opportunités du marché suggérées selon l'inspiration du moment. La truffe se décline toute l'année; vous profiterez d'un travail artisanal de la confection du pain à la réalisation de vos sorbets. Le diamant noir vous sera suggéré sous toutes ses formes, vous apprécierez  la Truffe dans tous ses états…

Côté restaurant, vous découvrirez un jardin verdoyant, un lieu exceptionnel et intimiste dédié à la sérénité,  une décoration intérieure réalisée avec goût et finesse. La cuisine ouverte permet de profiter des effluves gourmandes. Les maîtres mots « Partage & Convivialité ».

name: Black Bottle
offer: New Year's Eve Dinner Menu A$148
description:
Relaxed, authentic and local wine bar serving classic French bistro fare and delicious drops. A market influenced menu featuring fresh seafood, Australian cured meats and artisan cheeses.

An elegant wine bar that wouldn't be out of place in coastal France, Black Bottle focuses on exclusive ingredients and charcuterie and elevates them with unforgettable crushed grapes.

You might be in Sydney, but this darling little bistro transports you thousands of kilometers away to the vineyards of Europe. Maybe it's their rustic interior with homey wooden furnishings, exposed brick walls and all the grandeur of huge, arched doors that give it the impression of European sophistication. Maybe it's the pretty patio on which wine connoisseurs sip their way into the evening. Or maybe it's their sincere fascination with fine food and wine that has earned them such an esteemed reputation.

You are duly invited to live life to the fullest. Take the evening low and slow, savoring the rich flavors of chicken liver parfait with tangy beetroot and plum chutney, trout rillettes with capers and artisan cheese boards stuffed to the rafters with crackers and condiments.

Then, take on some mains, From Aylesbury duck breast to Tajima wagyu rump cap and lamb cutlets, this is thoughtful gastronomy served with a flourish. Ask your server for their wine recommendations. Armed with fine wines from across the globe, there's a bottle out there with your name on it. The question is, which one?

description:
What used to be an Art Gallery, where local artists displayed their 
work, is now a showcase of flavours. The Chef's culinary delights invite 
you on a journey across Portuguese cuisine. Traditional Portuguese 
cuisine, prepared with contemporary quality, precision and excellence. 
The restaurant's menu changes with the seasons, considering not only the 
values and traditions of Portuguese cuisine, but also our guests' 
dietary restrictions (vegetarian and gluten free).
